President Muhammadu Buhari has been urged to prevail on the Amnesty Office to pay salaries, money and stipends of vendors and ex- agitators. President and founder of Human Security Initiative For Peace and Development , Comrade David Reje,disclosed this in a statement yesterday. He stated that as a body committed  to the peace, security and development of the people , they had expressed appreciation to President Buhari for the prompt,  swift intervention and commitment to the fight against the Coronavirus (COVID – 19) pandemic ravaging the social, economic and political fabrics of all nations of the world. The group also appreciated the payment of the monthly stipends of ex-agitators,  and the palliative measures put in place to cushion the effect of the scorching hunger and starvation that is hiting hard on families at this critical moment of the  coronavirus. He said, “However, after taken stock of the happenstance, especially the chronic hunger and starvation that has permeated and the worst hit on the rural poor and so devastating on the vendors of the presidential amnesty programme (PAP) who borrowed money with interest to execute contracts that they have not been paid for. “These vendors and their chain of  dependants are in a crying shame as a result of the lockdown as a precautionary measure against the spread of the pandemic.Therefore,  we call on Mr.  President to order the payment,” he added. 